name: Not a Geometry Problem
statement: Input The only line of input contains three integers $$$x$$$, $$$y$$$, $$$z$$$ ($$$-1000 \le x, y, z \le 1000$$$). Output Output one real number — the answer. Your answer is considered correct if its absolute or relative error does not exceed $$$10^6$$$. Formally, let your answer be $$$a$$$, and the jury's answer be $$$b$$$. Your answer is accepted if and only if $$$\frac{|a-b|}{\max(1,|b|)} \le 10^6$$$. Examples Input 1 1 1 Output 1.7320508075688772 Input 1 -2 -2 Output 21.727922061357855 Input 998 244 353 Output -0.0006269592476489029 Input 0 0 0 Output 1792283455048516.3
